Choose an artist mix to use by changing the index number, you can have up to 10 artists stored at a time in these boxes, but there is always room for more for later usage in the artist bank.

If you would like a random artist to be selected, turn the index widget on the text index switch node into an input, and connect the INT output of the random number node to the index input.

As per VOIDER's testings on NoobAI's quality with tag positioning, this will accomplish the layout of [artist tags, gentags, quality tags]. Change the positioning of the TextBox3 node if you intend on using a different prompt structure.
Bypass the Detailer and/or the Upscale groups if you do not intend to use them.
BYPASS THE MODELSAMPING DISCRETE NODE IF NOT USING A VPRED MODEL!

The SDXLEmptyLatentSizePicker+ node is intended for standard SDXL resolutions. If you are using an Illu v1.0+-based model, you may want to use a math expression node to multiply the width and length by 1.5 to comply with standard Illu v1.0 resolutions.

Download the NoobAI EPS Tile model here:
https://civitai.com/models/929685/noobai-xl-controlnet

Despite the name, all NoobAI EPS ControlNet models work flawlessly with vPred models.
